  "caveats": [
    "The measured code state was clean commit eafb1e48828118334fbda391f4fec33099c39b42. Later docs-only cleanup does not change the measured engine code.",
    "The monitored runtime suite includes process-tree sampling and records one warm measured run per cell, so short-case throughput claims should be cross-checked against the direct CLI reruns in the same review root.",
    "The WSL deployment-shape rerun used a Linux checkout but wrote bundles back to /mnt/d, so replay and compare wall times are confounded by cross-filesystem I/O and should be read as deployment-shape evidence rather than unconditional Linux throughput proof.",
    "The Chris Roberts comparison is same-machine and matched on a shared no-op trader plus tick budget, but it is not full semantic parity.",
    "The shared-memory result is a transport microbenchmark only, not end-to-end Monte Carlo proof."
